Drop a 😍 if you’d wear this combo 👇🏾

Colorfix Featured:
Colorifx Mattes “Primary Blue”
Colorfix Mattes “Valentine”
Colorfix Foils “Venus”

How To Use Colorfix✨
- Use alone for a highly pigmented eye, lip or cheek.
- Layer beneath Metals or Micro Metals for a super rich color payoff and lots of dimensionality.
- Layer with ColorFix Glaze for a glossy finish.
- Use with a fine-tip brush for a budge-proof liner.
- Line, define and fill your lips for a pout that lasts.
- Mix in complexion products to adjust shades or to create a waterproof finish. 
- Achieve a dimensional highlight by tapping, swiping and blending a Metallic or Foil on the cheek.
- Use as a waterproof base for eyeshadow.
- This high-performance formula dries rapidly and should be blended quickly.
- Plays well with wax, silicone and oil-based products.

PRO Tip: Mix with Colorfix with Balm Powder for a blurring eye, lip or cheek color 💫

Tis the season to sparkle 🤩 Have you tried our Colorfix Metallics?

What It Colorfix? ✨
A supremely versatile, waterproof, crease-proof, richly pigmented multi-use hybrid cream color that can safely be used on lips, eyes or face. No fall-out. No creasing, No adhesive needed!

What are the 5 Colorfix finishes? ✨
- Mattes: Highly pigmented, matte color with extreme long-wear that can be used on eyes, cheek, or lips.
- Metallics: Full-coverage pigment with a pearly sheen, perfect for adding a subtle glow to eyes, cheeks or lips. Dries down matte.
- Foils: Ultra-shimmering finish with multi-dimensional, fine, glitter. Perfect as a topper or stand alone glow on the eyes or cheeks.
- Nudes: Matte shades inspired by skin tones in our best-selling foundations. Great as eyeliner, lipstick, contour, or spot coverage. Also perfect as a base for powders.
- Glazes: Long-wearing, glossy topper. Layer on top of other Colorfix finishes for a high-shine, crease-proof look.

What It Does ✨
Acts as a stand-alone eyeshadow, lip, or cheek, but also as a base for powder product. Optimized for a masterful color explosion.

How To Use Colorfix✨
- Use alone for a highly pigmented eye, lip or cheek.
- Mix with Balm Powder for a blurring eye, lip or cheek color.
- Layer beneath Metals or Micro Metals for a super rich color payoff and lots of dimensionality.
- Layer with ColorFix Glaze for a glossy finish.
- Use with a fine-tip brush for a budge-proof liner.
- Line, define and fill your lips for a pout that lasts.
- Mix in complexion products to adjust shades or to create a waterproof finish. 
- Achieve a dimensional highlight by tapping, swiping and blending a Metallic or Foil on the cheek.
- Use as a waterproof base for eyeshadow.
- This high-performance formula dries rapidly and should be blended quickly.
- Plays well with wax, silicone and oil-based products.

PRO Tip: Mix colors and finishes to create your own custom shades 💫

How are you experimenting with the different Colorfix finishes? 💫

What is Colorfix? ✨
A supremely versatile, waterproof, crease-proof, richly pigmented multi-use hybrid cream color that can safely be used on lips, eyes or face. No fall-out. No creasing, No adhesive needed!

What are the 5 Colorfix finishes? ✨
- Mattes: Highly pigmented, matte color with extreme long-wear that can be used on eyes, cheek, or lips.
- Metallics: Full-coverage pigment with a pearly sheen, perfect for adding a subtle glow to eyes, cheeks or lips. Dries down matte.
- Foils: Ultra-shimmering finish with multi-dimensional, fine, glitter. Perfect as a topper or stand alone glow on the eyes or cheeks.
- Nudes: Matte shades inspired by skin tones in our best-selling foundations. Great as eyeliner, lipstick, contour, or spot coverage. Also perfect as a base for powders.
- Glazes: Long-wearing, glossy topper. Layer on top of other Colorfix finishes for a high-shine, crease-proof look.

How To Use Colorfix✨
- Use alone for a highly pigmented eye, lip or cheek.
- Mix with Balm Powder for a blurring eye, lip or cheek color.
- Layer beneath Metals or Micro Metals for a super rich color payoff and lots of dimensionality.
- Layer with ColorFix Glaze for a glossy finish.
- Use with a fine-tip brush for a budge-proof liner.
- Line, define and fill your lips for a pout that lasts.
- Mix in complexion products to adjust shades or to create a waterproof finish. 
- Achieve a dimensional highlight by tapping, swiping and blending a Metallic or Foil on the cheek.
- Use as a waterproof base for eyeshadow.
- This high-performance formula dries rapidly and should be blended quickly.
- Plays well with wax, silicone and oil-based products.

PRO Tip: Layer a mix of different colors and textures to maximize your products while minimizing your kit/collection ❤️

Set your makeup without dimming your glow! Drop a 🤎 if you think you can try this 👇🏾

Makeup: @danessa_myricks
Muse: @Phenomenalkat

Step 1: Identify the areas of your face where you  notice your makeup creases the most. You’ll find that those areas may be around your eyes, along your laugh lines and the creases of your noses 

Step 2: Using a fluffy brush and feather like strokes, lightly dip into your favorite setting powder & tap off any excess. Remember that’s it’s always easier to add more setting powder later than it is to take away so only pick up what you’ll need!

Step 3: Gently press the bristles of your brush onto the areas where you crease the most. Remember to avoid the high points of your face because the goal is to strategically set while maintaining the glow you have build! 

I love to use @danessamyricksbeauty Evolution Powder because it’s microfine and maintains an extremely natural application.

The first of her kind, Blurring Balm Powder Flushed unique balm to powder formula is unlike anything you’ve tried before! 💫

What shade are you choosing? 👇🏾

✨Yummy Skin Blurring Balm Powder Flushed ✨ - $25

LAUNCHING 2/7 12AM EST

What It Is 
A buildable, soft-matte formula that blurs and smooths cheek and lip with all day wear.  This balm to powder is formulated with Upsalite technology for unrivaled blurring and oil control. This Swedish technology creates a soft focus, smoothing effect on pores and fine lines. 

Reason To Believe 
Upsalite: Supports and absorbs excess sebum and sweat while maintaining skin hydration.
Olive-Derived Squalane: Known to support oil production and diminish visible signs of aging.
Hyaluronic Acid: Promotes skin hydration.

Available in 6 universal shades designed to look great on every skin tone!
- GOLDEN HOUR - Vivid Orange Nectar
- PRIMADONNA - Vibrant Hot Pink
- DANCING QUEEN - Vivid Plum
- JUBILEE - Soft Terracotta 
- BELLINI - Poppy Golden Peach
- ROSÉ N BRUNCH - Neutral Rosey Pink

How To Use
- Swirl your fingers or a brush into the color. 
- Then, press onto your cheeks & lips. 
- Next, tap and blend for a fearless flush. 
- Repeat this step as many times as you’d like to build color.

Still deciding your #Fearlessflushed shade? Or have you found your go-to?🙋🏾‍♀️

✨Yummy Skin Blurring Balm Powder Flushed✨ - $25

Available in 6 universal shades designed to look great on every skin tone!
1. GOLDEN HOUR - Vivid Orange Nectar
2. PRIMADONNA - Vibrant Hot Pink
3. DANCING QUEEN - Vivid Plum
4. JUBILEE - Soft Terracotta 
5. BELLINI - Poppy Golden Peach
6. ROSÉ N BRUNCH - Neutral Rosey Pink

What It Is
A buildable, soft-matte formula that blurs and smooths cheek and lip with all day wear.  This balm to powder is formulated with Upsalite technology for unrivaled blurring and oil control. This Swedish technology creates a soft focus, smoothing effect on pores and fine lines. 

Reason To Believe 
Upsalite: Supports and absorbs excess sebum and sweat while maintaining skin hydration.
Olive-Derived Squalane: Known to support oil production and diminish visible signs of aging.
Hyaluronic Acid: Promotes skin hydration.

How To Use
It’s as simple as SWIRL, PRESS, TAP to BLEND & BLUR!
-Swirl your fingers or a brush into the color. 
-Then, press onto your cheeks & lips. 
-Next, tap and blend for a fearless flush. 
-Repeat this step as many times as you’d like to build color.

@ernestocasillas does it again 😍 Timeless glam using a full face of @danessamyricksbeauty on the beautiful @lijunli for Vanity Fair 🙏🏾❤️

“Li looking absolutely radiant for Vanity Fair ✨

I was inspired by the iridescent shine of Li's beautiful dress and I translated that onto her complexion using my Yummy Skin Complexión products @danessamyricksbeauty by @danessa_myricks. applied a generous amount of the Vision Flush Glow in the shade "Tiara" on the high points of her face. I paired the glow with flushed cheeks using Yummy Skin Blurred Balm Powder Flushed in the shade "Rosé n Brunch" available @sephora #partner

Product Breakdown:
- Yummy Skin Glow Serum In "Juice Boost"
- Yummy Skin Serum Foundation in shade 9N
- Vision Flush Glow in "Tiara"
- Balm Contour in Medium 1
- Blurring Balm Powder Flushed in "Rosè at Brunch"
- Evolution Powder 1 and 2”

#danessamyricksbeauty #danessamyricks #dmbeauty #vanityfairoscarparty #vanityfair

@xtina at the Vanity Fair Oscar Party with a full @danessamyricksbeauty face by the brilliant @etienneortega 😍

“XTINA looking stunning at last night #vanityfairoscarparty ✨

Makeup @etienneortega
Using @danessamyricksbeauty @danessa_myricks

I started with the yummy skin foundation in a mix of shades 10g and 13n to create the perfect color followed by blurring balm powder in shade 6 to add dimension to Xtinas complexion. For blush the "rose and brunch" blush to the apples of the cheek for a natural rose finish. Lastly added the illuminating veil liquid highlighter for a gorgeous glow✨

#yummyskin available at @sephora”

@lakeithstanfield3 and his fiancé @pink.kasmere stun in their matching full face of @danessamyricksbeauty by the amazing @taylourchanel 😍🙏🏾

“makeup by me for both @lakeithstanfield3 & @pink.kasmere x @vanityfair using @danessamyricksbeauty

Lakeith and his fiancée Kasmere wanted matching looks to compliment their matching YSL suiting, here's a breakdown of Lakeith's graphic liner and bleached brow look!

Lakeith:
- ��Started with a hydrating beauty oil to plump and prep the skin
- ��Continue prep with the Yummy Skin Blurring Balm Powder in
- Universal
- ��Color corrected with Colorfix in Carrot Top
- ��Use Vision Cream Cover buffed into the skin to even skin tone and create a flawless base
- ��Add a little Yummy Skin Blurring Balm Powder #8
- ��Create graphic eye using Colorfix Matte in Blackout
- ��Top the graphic base with Colorfix Foil in Nebula
- ��Using a disposable mascara wand, first pull Colorfix Nude 1 through the brows for a bleached effect
- ��Using a second mascara wand, top the now "bleached" brows with Colorfix Foil in Nebula
- ��Set face using Evolution Powder 3 & 4”

Did you hear that our nudes have been leaked? Starting April 21st, shop Colorfix Nudes at @sephora! 

What is Colorfix? ✨
A supremely versatile, waterproof, crease-proof, richly pigmented multi-use hybrid cream color that can safely be used on lips, eyes or face. No fall-out. No creasing, No adhesive needed!

What are Colorfix Nudes? ✨
Soft-matte shades inspired by skin tones from our best-selling foundation. Lift, prep, shade, outline and conceal every feature on the face! 

How To Use Colorfix✨
- Use as a waterproof base for eyeshadow to enhance the opacity and durability of eyeshadow powders. 
- Use alone for a highly pigmented eye, lip or cheek.
- For waterproof brows, use an angled brush to fill and define. 
- Mix with Balm Powder for a blurring eye, lip or cheek color.
- Layer with ColorFix Glaze for a glossy finish.
- Use with a fine-tip brush for a budge-proof classic liner or graphic shapes.
- Line, define and fill your lips for a plump pout that lasts.
- Layer with ColorFix Glaze for a glossy finish.
- This high-performance formula dries rapidly and should be blended quickly.
- Plays well with wax, silicone and oil-based products.

PRO Tip: Mix in complexion products to adjust shades or to create a waterproof finish.

Available online at @sephora 4/21 with select shades available in stores!

I am so excited to finally be able to share the newest addition to the @danessamyricksbeauty collection, Bi-Pride 💖💙 

To celebrate the one-year anniversary of our Infinite Chrome Flakes “Pride”. I have created another shade called “Bi-Pride,” in honor of the often marginalized bi community, comprised of color-shifting shades of blue, purple, and pink!

The LGBTQ+ community means so much to me, many of my best friends, co-collaborators, and family. My greatest sources of inspiration are individuals that identify as queer, as they bring love and bravery into this world. This is why I am so passionate about showing my support and admiration for LGBTQ+ people across the globe.

Our Infinite Chrome Flakes in “Pride” and “Bi-Pride” symbolize striving for a society where everyone (regardless of identity, expression, or orientation) can create and discover an inclusive realm of beauty without boundaries.

Bi-Pride launches 5/19 12AM EST at Danessamyricksbeauty.com and in-store & online at @sephora and @sephoracanada 

#danessamyricksbeauty #danessamyricks #dmbeauty #chromeflakes #pride #sephora #sephoracanda

To the incredible LGBTQIA+ community, you all mean so much to me and have been a constant source of inspiration and bravery. In creating @danessamyricksbeauty, I vowed to not only show my support and admiration, but to be a safe space in which everyone (regardless of their orientation or identity) can create freely and discover a world of beauty without boundaries! 

Beyond creating products, I see you, we see you and we hope you can see yourselves in everything we do here at DMB! 

To my beautiful DMB family, thank you for making Chrome Flakes our top selling color product at Sephora, none of this would be possible without your continued love and support!!

I developed shades for our NEW Yummy Skin Tint with your skin in mind.

Typically, most skin tints give a lightweight coverage, but once you add concealer, color corrector, etc., for more coverage, it defeats the product’s purpose.
 
That’s why I took the time to create your one-and-done Skin Tint that gives you just enough coverage to manage concerns like hyperpigmentation, difference in tones on the face, and redness all in one drop boosted with corrective pigments. 

We leaned into shades covering multiple skin tones ranging from fair to deep, focusing on corrective pigments for each skin tone’s concern while ensuring each shade was flexible.

Anytime I develop a complexion product, it’s with your skin in mind. I’ve done all the thinking for you, so you can skip your color correctors and concealers and go 😘

I woke up so grateful this morning.  I was thinking about my entrepreneurial  journey as a single mom of 2. The choices I made. The ups and downs. The uncertainty. The failures.
The stagnant times. The days I felt like I couldn’t do any more. The days I felt like I wanted to quit. 

I thought about all the opportunities lost, the people who have left.  I thought about all the stops and starts. All the pivots . I thought about all the things I wanted and all the moments I wondered if it would ever happen for me. Wondering if what I was creating mattered to anyone

I’m grateful that I had the courage to be patient. I’m grateful I kept on believing  in me.  I’m grateful for all of the things that went wrong because hindsight has shown me that it was part of the journey to making things right. It’s so clear to me that all of the moments, both good and bad are part of the of creation of something magical.  It’s all part of the journey. It’s all necessary  and important.

If you are reading this and feeling any bit of what I’ve felt please know that everything that is happening to you if for sure happening for you.  Never give up on you!

I love you.  Happy Sunday

Affirmations have always been a powerful tool for me to create a positive mindset. Repeating these affirmations daily helps me embody these qualities and embrace a more empowered and joyful life. 

My intention with naming each shade in Lightwork V was to let these words be a source of inspiration and encouragement.
 
✨RADIANT: “I am radiant, and my inner beauty shines brightly, lighting up the world around me.

✨CENTERED: “I am centered, finding tranquility within, no matter the chaos of the world.”

✨UNBREAKABLE: “I am unbreakable, my spirit forged in the fires of life’s challenges, emerging stronger than
ever.

✨ ENOUGH: “I am enough just as I am, and I embrace my uniqueness and inherent worth.”

✨FIERCE/FEARLESS: “I am fierce and fearless, fear is my fuel, and courage is my compass.”

 ✨LOVED/HEALED: “I am loved and healed, and I extend love and healing to myself and all those in my life.”

As you swipe each shade on, embody the feeling of the accompanying affirmation and believe you are the representation of that shade.

I’ve learned the power of the words “I am,” and I want to share that magic with you !

Saying the words I am with belief is like saying Abracadabra. I’ve learned through my ongoing spiritual and mental health journey that we can choose to use the words to empower or disempower.  I think of how many times I looked in the mirror and said I’m ugly, I’m fat,  I’m tired, or I’m old. These words that flew so easily from my lips did nothing but dim my spirit and my light.  I’ve learned to make speaking affirming words a daily practice, choosing words that uplift, and allow me to access my power and stand in the light 

I created this palette for me and you as a reminder to be gentle with ourselves, especially in those moments alone when we prepare ourselves to get ready to face the world. We can say things that light us up, empower, and heal.
Our words are our armor; they have so much power.  Whether you speak them or write them, the impact is profound. 

I’ve closed my mind and imagined you and me looking in the mirror, swiping these magical colors all over the face, and saying the words aloud: I am fearless, I am strong, etc.

I hope this palette and its empowering affirmations help you to manifest the most magical version of yourselves as you say it, swipe it, believe it.

Xo Danessa ❤️

“I just try to be gentle with myself, and also to be empathetic and appreciative for how that person added to who I am right now and where they brought me in my journey…”

Leading with love was a strong theme in this recent conversation with Danessa that took me to a whole other level. 

@danessa_myricks is one of the most curious people I’ve ever met, full of ideas and innovation she consistently bet on herself year after year. With over 20 years in the game she has created classes for people to learn how to do makeup, sold DVDs, traveled by CAR to trade shows all around the country. 

Her brand started from inside her home in the basement scooping pigment into jars. She now has a brand that is available worldwide and in every Sephora in both Canada and the USA. 

She is a pioneer for the artist community and a champion for using makeup as an expression of how YOU FEEL. 

She has one of the warmest energies in our industry. 
Her existence has makes me feel seen and welcome and inspires me to keep going. It was an absolute honor to spend time with her and talk about how her incredible time in self discovery has transformed her ability to lead and guide herself and her team @danessamyricksbeauty. 

I hope you LOVE this conversation as much as it filled my heart, mind and soul.

*Finding, building, and trusting your team
*Marketing strategy, operations, and product quality

I find myself reflecting on the power of dreams and the role we each play in carrying them forward. 

My dream has always been more than creating beauty products; it’s about amplifying every voice and celebrating every story. 

‘I am a reflection of this dream’ is a mantra that echoes in every step of my journey as an artist, a founder, a mother, and a Black woman. 

 I stand on the shoulders of giants like Dr. King, who paved the way for us to have a voice, to be seen, and to make an impact.

As I reflect on this ongoing dream and journey, let us remember that 
Our voices, stories, and beauty are the reflections of the dream that Martin Luther King Jr. spoke of. 

We all have the power to dream, inspire, and create a world where every voice is heard, and every story is celebrated.
